      • runTesterGivenOnSuccessiveConjunctionsOfLiterals

        public static void runTesterGivenOnSuccessiveConjunctionsOfLiterals(java.lang.String problemName,
                                                                    com.sri.ai.grinder.tester.SGDPLLTTester.TestRunner tester,

                                                                    java.util.function.Function<Constraint,Expression> makeRandomLiteralGivenConstraint,
                                                                    boolean outputCount,
                                                                    Context context)
                                                             throws java.lang.Error
        Generates a number of tests based on a conjunction each, which is formed by incrementally adding literals to it. The conjunction is provided to a TestRunner which runs some test based on it. Throws an Error with the failure description if a test fails.
        Parameters:
        tester - the TestRunner
        numberOfTests - the number of tests to run
        maxNumberOfLiterals - the maximum number of literals to add to each test conjunction
        theoryTestingSupport -
        makeInitialConstraint - a thunk generating new constraints equivalent to TRUE
        makeRandomLiteralGivenConstraint - a function generating appropriate new literals (given generated constraint if needed)
        outputCount - whether to output the test count
        context - a context
        Throws:
        java.lang.Error
